(3, 'Ashraf Hossan Shovo', 20, 'Html timeline inside TR tag', 'Computer', '<p>Hello Guys,<br />I am trying to put a timeline inside a table row</p>\r\n<p>this is the code :</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://jsfiddle.net/fpvgtayw/">https://jsfiddle.net/fpvgtayw/</a></p>\r\n<p>Basically what i want is to make the timeline connected/joined without any gap created because of td cells.</p>\r\n<p>Need help. Thanks</p>', '2016-12-16 19:57:55', 3, 1),
(3, 'Ashraf Hossan Shovo', 21, 'Wifi Connections', 'Network', '<p>i have 2 laptops (1 new), 1 samsung smart tv, 2 cell phones all using wifi and everything was fine until a few days ago.<br />I have a cable modem connected to the wifi router Wan port.<br />The wifi router is about 8 years old.<br />Now, the older laptop will only connect to wifi if and only if TV wifi is running, sometimes not even with that. The wifi runs ok at work.<br />The newer laptop does work sometimes with both TV on or off.<br />All devices are set to acquire dynamic ip and dhcp addresses.<br />I have tried shutting down and rebooting everything many times to isolate the problem but so far cannot understand dependency on the TV.</p>', '2016-12-16 20:01:53', 2, 1),
(4, 'Suhin Ahmed', 22, ' RAM upgrade', 'Computer', '<p>I had an emachine running vista home that died on me so I gutted it for parts, drives and memory. I recently had a dell dimension 2400 given to me that I am using now but it runs very slow. I know by doing a system scan of the memory that it has 2 x 512mb of memory in it now. I pulled 3 samsung 1GB 1Rx8 PC2-6400u-666-12-ZZ out of the emachine can I use this memory in the Dell to increase performance?</p>', '2016-12-16 20:05:18', 0, 1),
(3, 'Ashraf Hossan Shovo', 23, 'Help!! Bluetooth Headphones Stopped Working!', 'Electronics ', '<p>Ok, so I''ve had a pair of Bluetooth Ecandy Headphones (The box calls them ''4-in-1'') for about 6 months now, but I''ve recently been experiencing problems. All sound is no longer transmitted through the headphones, but through the device speakers, while the Bluetooth appears to still be connected. Furthermore, none of the buttons are responding, so there is no way to turn off, or reset the headset. The only indication that it isn''t completely dead is that the power light is still on.<br />After establishing that there was no problem with the Bluetooth connection, I let the battery run flat (I didn''t really have a choice) and charged them up again. They seemed to work fine, afterwards, but the fault quickly reappeared. Upon gently taking the headset apart, little seemed wrong, however, I discovered a loose, black wire, only connected at one end, but cannot see where the other end should be soldered to. Presumably this is the cause? Any advice would be appreciated, and pictures will follow.<br />Here''s the link to the headset I have.</p>', '2016-12-17 01:44:42', 1, 1),
(1, 'Mahbub Rahman', 24, 'Amazon Launches Web-storage Service for Music', 'Internet', '<p><span style="color: #333333; font-family: ''lucida grande'',''lucida sans unicode'',geogrotesque,arial,verdana,tahoma,sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #e9ecee; display: inline ! important; float: none;"><em style="color: #000000; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Ahead of both Google and Apple, Amazon has launched a couple of Web-based services that allow users to both store their music (and other data) in the cloud, and listen to it, either on the go or while at home. The first component is called "Cloud Drive", and is just as it sounds... a service for storage space on the Web. For all users, the first 5GB of storage space is free, and upgrades can be had in increments, with all packages being priced at an effective $1 per GB.</em></span></p>', '2016-12-17 01:52:34', 0, 1),
(3, 'Ashraf Hossan Shovo', 25, 'Laptop Wireless Connection Problem', 'Network', '<p>Hi Everyone,<br />I''m working on a friends laptop at the mo and it won''t wirelessly connect to my hub.<br /><br />Laptop Model : HP compaq NX9030<br /><br />The laptop has recently been wiped clean and a fresh install of Win XP c/w SP3 has been done.<br />The additional drivers were downloaded from :<br /><br /><a href="http://h20564.www2.hp.com/hpsc/swd/public/readIndex?sp4ts.oid=441564&amp;swLangOid=8&amp;swEnvOid=228" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Drivers &amp; Software for HP Compaq nx9030 Notebook PC - HP Support Center.</a><br /><br />Although, that said, I wasn''t sure which Network driver to go for so I just picked one and am not sure if that is related to my problem.<br /><br />Basically, the issue I am having is that using windows wireless connection program, it sees the hub and shows it at full strength, accepts the password but will not finally connect. It just keeps on trying but then gives up and I have to then select the hub in the list, hit connect, input the password and the same thing happens ??<br /><br />Can anyone shed some light on it for me please, I would be most grateful.<br /><br />Many Thanks</p>', '2016-12-17 01:54:38', 2, 1),
(2, 'Mujibur Rahman', 26, 'Can you recommend a portable battery pack?', 'Mobile', '<p>I have a Samsung Galaxy Note 4 and I''m looking for a portable battery pack because I can no longer use my it for a whole day without it dying. I found a review for a JETech battery pack, but I wanted to know if there are any better for a reasonable price.&nbsp;<br /><br />Here''s the review I was looking at&nbsp;</p>', '2016-12-17 01:58:05', 2, 1),
(3, 'Ashraf Hossan Shovo', 27, 'Please Help..What''s the best router to buy for VOIP business', 'Network', '<p>Hello Fellow IT''s,<br /><br />I am helping my friend out with his network configuration for optimal operation for VOIP operations his business. It s a simple set up, in which there are 27 client computers and 1 network server running windows server 2008 R2. Right now there is no router in between the Comcast modem and switch just a direct connection between the two devices. The modem handles the DHCP and is the default gateway. I''m trying to find the correct router that I can implement into this situation; Preferably one that I can set up a firewall, VPN, and that has QoS. The computers all use OS based soft phones and the databases are accessed and utilized through the cloud. I''ve done some research and found a few I believe that may work in this network but not sure. I was also informed that bandwidth plays a part in the selection and I have the overall numbers and system specs to provide as necessary. I have a few links below of a some routers that I found.<br /><br />SOHO Network Security Firewall:<br /><br />Cisco Small Business RV320 and RV325 Dual Gigabit WAN VPN Routers.<br /><br />Basically all I''m trying to do is protect the system, decease latency, increased call quality, and allow for remote access to the network.<br /><br />Any help would be greatly appreciated, and thank you.</p>', '2016-12-17 02:04:05', 0, 1);

