(29, 1, 20, 'Mahbub Rahman', '<p><span style="color: #333333; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; display: inline !important; float: none;">Why not just put the green border on the table, and then re-align the ticks slightly to suit?</span></p>', 0x696d6167652f, '2016-12-16'),
(30, 1, 20, 'Mahbub Rahman', '<p><span style="color: #333333; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; display: inline !important; float: none;">Brilliant solution<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><a class="mention" style="background: #f5f5f5; color: #707070; text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; word-wrap: break-word; padding: 2px 4px; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 0.93em; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" href="https://www.sitepoint.com/community/users/ralphm">@mahbub</a><span style="color: #333333; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; display: inline !important; float: none;">!<span class="Apple-converted-space"> <br /></span></span></p>', 0x696d6167652f, '2016-12-16'),
(31, 3, 21, 'Ashraf Hossan Shovo', '<p>Have you tried a new router?</p>\r\n<p>These can fail in odd ways.</p>', 0x696d6167652f, '2016-12-16'),
(32, 4, 21, 'Suhin Ahmed', '<p>Not yet</p>\r\n<p>i had the same no of devices for two years.&nbsp;<br />replaced one laptop with a new laptop but that worked fine for a week too.<br />the weird part is the TV is always able to connect to the wifi ... thought the wifi router and tv are in different rooms.<br />also now it looks like the wifi on the old laptop will also connect if the ethernet is connected but will drop if i take out the lan cable.<br />i shutdown everything and powered down the TV and reset the cable modem and router - then booted the laptop - still nothing.<br />i wanted to ask if there is some reason before going and buying a new router.</p>', 0x696d6167652f, '2016-12-16'),
(33, 1, 23, 'Mahbub Rahman', '<p><span style="color: #000000; font-family: Panton, sans-serif; font-size: 23.9999px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; display: inline !important; float: none;">I think you found the cause.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000; font-family: Panton, sans-serif; font-size: 23.9999px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; display: inline !important; float: none;"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: ''Proxima Nova'', Proxima-Nova, proxima-nova, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; display: inline !important; float: none;">I don''t see any online documents about inside the product. If you have any electronics engineering friends let them try to fix but in this case check your warranty (like void as you opened it ) and then shop for a new set.</span></span></p>', 0x696d6167652f, '2016-12-16'),
(34, 2, 25, 'Mujibur Rahman', '<p>pen up Device Manager<br /><br />On everything that has a yellow exclamation mark, do the following:&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />Right click -&gt; Properties -&gt; Details tab<br /><br />Post the following info for each item that has a yellow exclamation mark:&nbsp;<br />Under "Hardware Ids" in the dropdown, it should have something like VEN_####&amp;DEV#### ; post that section, where #### = some alphanumeric combination.</p>', 0x696d6167652f, '2016-12-16'),
(35, 3, 25, 'Ashraf Hossan Shovo', '<p>Ok, will do and will get right back :-)<br />Thanks</p>', 0x696d6167652f, '2016-12-16'),
(36, 1, 26, 'Mahbub Rahman', '<p>I''m sure that one is pretty decent but I''ve owned several of those type of battery packs and, due to their size, they''re not as portable as you would expect. I often ended up not having the battery pack with me when I needed it.<br />I currently carry one of these: Emergency Keychain Charger by Pulsepak &raquo; Review. I carry it on my keychain so it''s always with me when I''m out and about. It''s not the most powerful battery pack available but, imo, it''s the most convenient. One feature I especially like is that it doesn''t require a cable to charge your phone, it has a micro USB connector built-in. With other battery packs you have to make sure you carry the charger cord as well as battery which makes it less portable.<br />With all of these battery packs, you need to remember to keep the pack charged, nothing worse then pulling out your battery backup only to find out you forgot to recharge it!</p>', 0x696d6167652f, '2016-12-16'),
(37, 3, 26, 'Ashraf Hossan Shovo', '<p>You can get many different batteries and size from say 2600mAh (1 charge) to 50,000mAh (as big as phone, around upto around 25 charges).<br /><br />for 50,000mAh battery your looking at around &pound;20ish, but can never be sure how much capacity these labelled battery actually hold.</p>', 0x696d6167652f, '2016-12-16'),
(38, 2, 1, 'Mujibur Rahman', '<p>I dont know</p>', 0x696d6167652f, '2016-12-25');

